Patricia Cutts https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patricia_Cutts 0 Patricia "Pat" Cutts (20 July 1926 – 6 September 1974) was an English film and television actress. She was the first person to portray the character of Blanche Hunt in ITV soap opera Coronation Street, appearing in two episodes. After her death, Maggie Jones took over the role.
